WEBVTT

00:00.700 --> 00:03.102
Sally: Daniel! I cannot wait
till you meet your maker!

00:03.104 --> 00:06.405
What if the man was murdered
and no one finds out about it.

00:06.407 --> 00:07.573
You have to trust me.

00:07.575 --> 00:09.108
No, actually, I don't.

00:09.110 --> 00:11.276
Adnan salif says hello.
Keep your phone on, "h."

00:11.278 --> 00:13.145
Huck: Quinn,
you've been a bad girl.

00:13.147 --> 00:14.279
You're not a gladiator
anymore.

00:14.281 --> 00:16.047
[ screaming ]
olivia: You hurt her.

00:16.050 --> 00:17.116
I had to make her
tell the truth.

00:17.118 --> 00:18.717
She was working
for your father.

00:18.719 --> 00:21.353
Don't worry, sweetheart.
I'll see you real soon.

00:21.355 --> 00:23.756
Your father has to be stopped,
'cause I need answers.

00:23.758 --> 00:27.426
I have never answered
to any holder of your office.

00:27.428 --> 00:29.528
That changes right here,
right now.

00:29.530 --> 00:32.031
I'm command now,
effective immediately.
The hell you are.

00:32.033 --> 00:33.365
I'm gonna have to ask my agents
to escort you to the street.

00:33.367 --> 00:35.534
I'm running against you
as an independent.

00:35.536 --> 00:37.369
Fitz: You're making
the biggest mistake

00:37.371 --> 00:38.437
Of your life crossing me.

00:38.439 --> 00:40.739
See you
on the battlefield.

00:42.108 --> 00:44.309
[ indistinct conversations ]

00:51.451 --> 00:53.752
She's running!

00:53.754 --> 00:55.087
Reporter: ...Waiting
for what is nothing short

00:55.089 --> 00:58.190
Reporter #2: The resignation
of a sitting vice president

00:58.192 --> 00:59.825
Hasn't happened since 1973,

00:59.827 --> 01:03.429
Reporter #3:
The timing of vice president
langston's resignation

01:03.431 --> 01:05.096
Could not have come
at a worse time.

01:05.099 --> 01:06.598
Confidence
in the grant administration

01:06.600 --> 01:08.267
Is plummeting as a veritable
revolution plays out.

01:08.269 --> 01:10.102
Reporter #4: We are live
at the white house

01:10.104 --> 01:11.737
As we await
the resignation address

01:11.739 --> 01:13.839
From vice president
sally langston.

01:13.841 --> 01:15.240
[ reporters talking ]

01:15.242 --> 01:18.243
So, what is it?
What's our message?

01:18.245 --> 01:20.512
Cyrus, I have the entire
press corps waiting for me!

01:20.514 --> 01:22.214
We're waiting on
the poll numbers.

01:22.216 --> 01:24.783
Do we call her a traitor?
We're waiting.

01:24.785 --> 01:30.456
Her already-shaky mental state
suffering a deadly blow

01:30.458 --> 01:34.593
Sexist but effective.
Leak that on deep background --

01:34.595 --> 01:36.095
We're not leaking anything.
We're waiting.

01:36.097 --> 01:37.429
While we wait, the press corps
thinks I'm hiding,

01:37.431 --> 01:38.464
And they're not wrong.

01:38.466 --> 01:39.731
The numbers
are the oracle.

01:39.733 --> 01:41.266
The numbers will tell us
what to --

01:41.268 --> 01:43.368
What numbers?
The polls!

01:43.370 --> 01:46.205
Someone bring me
the damn polls right now.
Yes, sir.

01:46.207 --> 01:47.806
The distribution list
was limited.

01:47.808 --> 01:51.577
Sir, well, the president --
faster, ethan, faster.

01:51.579 --> 01:53.112
The president wanted to review
the numbers with --

01:53.114 --> 01:54.780
With whom?
With whom, ethan?

01:54.782 --> 01:56.849
With his
new campaign manager.

02:01.754 --> 02:02.821
[ knock on door ]

02:06.759 --> 02:08.327
The rest
of your campaign team

02:08.329 --> 02:10.162
Would like to see
the poll numbers...

02:10.163 --> 02:11.497
When you get a minute.

02:11.499 --> 02:20.272
[ door closes ]

02:20.274 --> 02:22.274
Remember --
calm, measured.

02:22.276 --> 02:23.842
Before the last word
leaves your lips,

02:23.844 --> 02:27.212
Are gonna be blasting you
for being a spiteful squatter

02:27.214 --> 02:29.214
Suffering from a wicked case
of hot flashes,

02:29.216 --> 02:30.249
But you're not.

02:30.251 --> 02:31.717
You are standing up
for the people

02:31.719 --> 02:35.721
Against the tyranny
of a decadent monarch, plus...

02:35.723 --> 02:37.556
You know,
jesus loves you.

02:37.558 --> 02:39.224
Yes.
Yes, I can do this.
Yeah.

02:39.226 --> 02:41.193
Mm-hmm.
Two-minute warning.

02:41.195 --> 02:44.763
Not a big chance,
but a fighting chance.

02:44.765 --> 02:47.266
So, these are
your talking points.

02:47.268 --> 02:50.369
Number one -- sally langston's
a selfish quitter.

02:50.371 --> 02:52.271
She abandoned
her views on abortion,

02:52.273 --> 02:53.705
And now
she's abandoning her post.

02:53.707 --> 02:55.440
Number two --
sally's a loose cannon,

02:55.442 --> 02:59.611
A fundamentalist extremist
who's incapable of compromise.

02:59.613 --> 03:02.514
Three -- sally's endangering
our national security

03:02.516 --> 03:05.184
And the safety of our
brave troops serving overseas.

03:05.186 --> 03:11.523
Which is why this country needs
to band together immediately

03:11.525 --> 03:14.893
And show our unwavering support
to our commander-in-chief.

03:14.895 --> 03:17.329
So, selfish quitter,
loose cannon,

03:17.331 --> 03:18.797
Endangering our troops.

03:18.799 --> 03:20.399
Stick to those talking points.

03:20.401 --> 03:24.269
And we will come out of this
stronger than ever.

03:24.271 --> 03:25.270
[ applause ]

03:25.272 --> 03:27.773
Sally:
<i>My fellow americans,</i>

03:27.775 --> 03:29.775
<i>As we know from</i>
<i>our nation's great history,</i>

03:29.777 --> 03:32.578
<i>There are times when</i>
<i>political bonds must be broken</i>

03:32.580 --> 03:34.279
To preserve
the will of the people

03:34.281 --> 03:36.748
And the freedoms
we hold so dear.

03:36.750 --> 03:40.852
Like our founding fathers,
I have been witness to tyranny.

03:40.854 --> 03:44.356
I believe our president's moral
corruption knows no bounds.

03:44.358 --> 03:46.992
<i>And so, as of this morning,</i>

03:46.994 --> 03:49.895
<i>I am declaring my independence</i>
<i>from president grant</i>

03:49.897 --> 03:52.898
<i>So that I may run</i>
<i>as a third-party candidate</i>

03:52.900 --> 03:55.267
<i>In the upcoming election.</i>

03:55.269 --> 03:58.270
<i>However, because of my duties</i>
<i>to god and my country,</i>

03:58.272 --> 04:01.240
<i>To the whims</i>
<i>of its childish leader.</i>

04:01.242 --> 04:06.245
This is why I cannot and will
not resign as vice president.

04:06.247 --> 04:08.680
<i>Turn out the lights</i>
<i>on his irresponsibility...</i>

04:08.682 --> 04:12.551
As you lie through your
opportunistic duplicitous teeth!

04:12.553 --> 04:14.820
How could she do this?
She can't <i>do</i> this.

04:14.822 --> 04:15.988
She is.

04:15.990 --> 04:18.523
<i>Thank you for your support.</i>

04:18.524 --> 04:21.692
<i>May god bless you,</i>
<i>and may god continue to bless</i>

04:21.695 --> 04:24.896
<i>The United States of america.</i>

04:24.898 --> 04:26.265
Shocking move
by the vice president

04:26.267 --> 04:27.399
To split the ticket,
leave the party,

04:27.401 --> 04:28.734
And run against her boss,

04:28.736 --> 04:30.936
All while refusing
to leave the west wing.

04:30.938 --> 04:33.472
It's certainly historic,
but not unprecedented.

04:33.474 --> 04:35.741
In the 1800 election,
vice president thomas jefferson

04:35.743 --> 04:37.809
Ran against
president john adams.

04:37.811 --> 04:38.944
Legally, langston is
well within her rights,

04:38.946 --> 04:41.747
And a very unpopular
president grant

04:41.749 --> 04:44.516
Through congress
to remove her from office.

04:44.518 --> 04:47.286
He simply doesn't have
the political capital.

04:47.288 --> 04:49.921
Fitz.

04:49.923 --> 04:51.290
[ sighs ]

04:51.292 --> 04:52.858
Cyrus: Sir,
with all due respect --

04:52.860 --> 04:54.026
[ glass shatters ]

04:54.028 --> 04:56.028
[ gasps ]

04:56.030 --> 04:56.995
Do something!

04:56.997 --> 04:59.031
He listens to you.

04:59.033 --> 05:03.568
Fitz, you need to stop drinking.
It's not even lunchtime.

05:03.570 --> 05:06.972
What if iran
declares war on us?

05:06.974 --> 05:08.040
Why don't you ask sally?

05:08.042 --> 05:10.976
Fitz.

05:10.978 --> 05:14.446
Fitz, look at me!

05:14.448 --> 05:16.715
Yes, this is a setback,

05:16.717 --> 05:18.383
But we simply need to change
the conversation,

05:18.385 --> 05:19.718
Get the ball
back in our court,

05:19.720 --> 05:21.053
And shore up our support
with the base.

05:21.055 --> 05:22.554
We can achieve
both those goals

05:22.556 --> 05:23.722
With the right
vice-presidential pick.

05:23.724 --> 05:25.090
Now, cyrus and I
have drawn up a list --

05:25.092 --> 05:26.925
I've already chosen
a new vice president --

05:26.927 --> 05:31.963
Nichols?
The governor of california?

05:31.965 --> 05:33.465
Your former lieutenant governor
of california.

05:33.467 --> 05:39.438
Get andy on the line.
I'll ask him myself.

05:39.440 --> 05:42.941
Fitz, aside from the fact
you hail from the same state,

05:42.943 --> 05:45.944
Nichols is a straight,
white man at a point in time

05:45.946 --> 05:47.479
When you <i>desperately</i>
<i>need to highlight diversity</i>

05:47.481 --> 05:51.516
Andrew nichols is a man
who has worked under me before.

05:51.518 --> 05:53.785
He's a man who is loyal
and whom I can trust.

05:53.787 --> 05:55.620
Fitz,
he is a good man,

05:55.622 --> 05:57.923
But I just don't see
how he serves --

05:57.925 --> 06:01.360
Call nichols today
or I will.

06:01.362 --> 06:02.661
That's all.

06:12.038 --> 06:13.772
I said, "that's all."

06:20.747 --> 06:22.013
Cyrus...

06:22.015 --> 06:23.715
I have committed a sin.

06:23.717 --> 06:26.451
<i>It's daniel douglas.</i>

06:26.453 --> 06:27.886
<i>He's -- he's --</i>
<i>I'm forsaken, cyrus.</i>

06:27.888 --> 06:29.855
<i>My flesh,</i>
<i>it's venal and despised.</i>

06:29.857 --> 06:33.024
<i>I fear it's time.</i>
<i>I have to give myself over.</i>

06:33.026 --> 06:35.694
Cyrus: <i>Sally!</i>
<i>It is not time.</i>

06:35.696 --> 06:39.030
Do not give yourself over.
<i>D-do not move.</i>

06:39.032 --> 06:40.866
<i>Do not call anyone.</i>
<i>I am coming to you right now.</i>

06:40.868 --> 06:42.401
[ beep ]

06:42.403 --> 06:44.569
First, I'm sorry.
You were right.

06:44.571 --> 06:45.871
She's pretty much admitting
she murdered her husband.

06:45.873 --> 06:47.739
Where did
you get that tape?

06:47.741 --> 06:49.875
Doesn't matter.
We can't use it -- inadmissible.

06:49.877 --> 06:51.543
Well, in that case,
I guess we're done here.

06:51.545 --> 06:53.011
What? No. Sit down.

06:53.013 --> 06:55.180
I have a job now, rosen,
in the white house.

06:55.182 --> 06:57.082
And if you haven't noticed,
our plate's pretty full today.

06:57.084 --> 06:58.750
That's just it.
You're on the inside now.

06:58.752 --> 07:00.619
You're privy
to everything they say.

07:00.621 --> 07:02.187
We just need
one unguarded moment

07:02.189 --> 07:03.688
And we can
nail these bastards.

07:03.690 --> 07:07.025
Is this your m.O. -- You storm
into someone's office,

07:07.027 --> 07:08.427
Give them the story
of the century,

07:08.429 --> 07:11.730
Because you've pulled this crap
on me twice now.

07:11.732 --> 07:13.598
I came to you a month ago
with my suspicions,

07:13.600 --> 07:15.734
And you didn't want to hear it,
so I dropped it.

07:15.736 --> 07:17.002
You should do the same.

07:17.004 --> 07:18.670
So, your husband gives you
a sweet government job

07:18.672 --> 07:21.673
And you walk right on over
to the dark side.

07:21.675 --> 07:24.609
Yes, my husband gave me
a sweet government job.

07:24.611 --> 07:27.446
And how exactly does that differ
from what he did for you?

07:27.448 --> 07:28.914
[ cellphone ringing ]

07:28.916 --> 07:30.749
[ door opens, closes ]

07:30.751 --> 07:32.017
[ beep ]
rosen.

07:32.019 --> 07:33.852
This is harrison wright.
I need a favor.
No.

07:33.854 --> 07:35.687
You haven't
even heard it yet.

07:35.689 --> 07:38.824
An old friend of mine just
got a visa to come back in

07:38.826 --> 07:40.792
The United States,
named adnan salif.

07:40.794 --> 07:43.795
Can you look into it?
Still no.

07:43.797 --> 07:44.863
I'm serious, rosen.
Please.

07:44.865 --> 07:46.965
I'll see what I can do.

07:46.967 --> 07:48.633
[ sighs ]

07:48.635 --> 07:50.869
Charlie: After that,
I was pretty much

07:50.871 --> 07:52.838
Persona non grata
in brazil.

07:52.840 --> 07:55.874
Well, all of south america.
Olé, right?

07:55.876 --> 07:58.210
So, that's when I hooked up
with the agency --

07:58.212 --> 08:00.178
A steady paycheck
doing something I loved.

08:00.180 --> 08:02.881
Killed two birds...
And some people.

08:02.883 --> 08:05.884
Well, I'm sure
you'll see that in the file.

08:05.886 --> 08:07.719
As the new command, I'm sitting
down with all the agents

08:07.721 --> 08:09.521
To make sure there aren't
gonna be any problems.

08:09.523 --> 08:11.690
Are there going to be
any problems, charlie?

08:11.692 --> 08:12.824
I take orders from
whoever's wearing the badge.

08:12.826 --> 08:13.925
Keeps it simple.

08:13.927 --> 08:16.895
Good to hear.

08:19.832 --> 08:23.702
One more thing --
quinn perkins.

08:23.704 --> 08:25.003
Is that a name
I should know?

08:26.239 --> 08:28.740
She's a good kid.

08:28.742 --> 08:31.243
Hit a rough patch.
I've been looking out for her.

08:31.245 --> 08:33.912
What can I say?
Mr. Softy.

08:33.914 --> 08:35.746
I don't know what arrangements
were made before I arrived,

08:35.749 --> 08:38.750
But quinn perkins is not b613,
never will be.

08:38.751 --> 08:41.086
And if anything happens
to her --

08:41.087 --> 08:44.022
Say no more, boss.
No rocking the boat here.

08:46.759 --> 08:49.060
Andrew nichols,
governor of california,

08:49.062 --> 08:51.062
Former lieutenant governor
under grant.
♪ express yourself

08:51.064 --> 08:52.764
Governor nichols,
I'm sorry for all the secrecy.

08:52.766 --> 08:54.766
I'm sure you understand
the sensitivity of this meeting.

08:54.768 --> 08:56.101
♪ you don't ever need help
from nobody else ♪

08:56.103 --> 08:57.636
Riding over here
in the trunk of a sedan

08:57.638 --> 08:58.904
Isn't my favorite way
to travel,

08:58.906 --> 09:00.672
But if it's in service
of president grant,

09:00.674 --> 09:04.075
What's his record?
First term was a success.

09:04.077 --> 09:05.810
♪ express yourself
reduced emissions,
balanced the budget,

09:05.812 --> 09:08.880
Actresses, models,
talk-show hosts, you name it.

09:08.882 --> 09:10.815
Oh, right.
So he's a playboy.
♪ do it good

09:10.817 --> 09:17.622
♪ it's not what you look like
to run for the vice president
of the United States --

09:17.624 --> 09:23.395
♪ it's what you're doing
when you're doing ♪
joining this ticket now,
you'd be saddling yourself

09:23.397 --> 09:29.601
My brand? I wouldn't
be governor -- <i>anything.</i>

09:29.603 --> 09:32.637
I wouldn't have a brand if
it weren't for fitzgerald grant.
♪ express yourself

09:32.639 --> 09:34.739
The president
is asking me to serve.

09:34.741 --> 09:36.741
I could never
turn my back on that.
♪ oh!

09:36.743 --> 09:40.312
Not much. Never married.
No shady real-estate deals.

09:40.314 --> 09:41.913
♪ express yourself
dems spent a fortune
on oppo research

09:41.915 --> 09:43.782
In the last campaign
and came up empty.

09:43.784 --> 09:45.750
He's clean.
All right.

09:45.752 --> 09:47.986
Let's test the ticket.
Let's poll him.

09:47.988 --> 09:49.688
♪ express yourself

09:49.690 --> 09:53.358
With men.
They trust him to take over,
should, god forbid --

09:53.360 --> 09:54.893
He'll never
have the chance.

09:54.895 --> 09:58.663
And single girls
of their boyfriend who did.

09:58.665 --> 10:00.832
And sally langston will think
christmas came early.

10:00.834 --> 10:03.635
My solution is for you
to talk him out of it.

10:03.637 --> 10:05.770
Impossible. He's closing ranks.
Loyalty above all.

10:05.772 --> 10:08.807
[ sighs ]
it's why he put jake ballard
in charge of b613.

10:08.809 --> 10:10.108
He did what?

10:10.110 --> 10:12.143
[ sighs ]
I assumed you knew.

10:12.145 --> 10:13.979
No.

10:16.382 --> 10:18.650
Dad?

10:18.652 --> 10:21.152
Olivia?

10:21.154 --> 10:23.755
How did you know
that I would be here?

10:23.757 --> 10:28.059
It's where you used to
take me after mom...

10:28.061 --> 10:30.295
After I thought
she died.

10:30.297 --> 10:35.133
Would take their children
to the playground?
They do.

10:35.135 --> 10:36.901
But I liked it here.

10:36.903 --> 10:40.705
I liked the quote.

10:40.940 --> 10:44.809
"uncommon valor
was a common virtue."

10:44.811 --> 10:48.980
I like it, too.

10:48.982 --> 10:51.983
It used to remind me
of mom.

10:51.985 --> 10:54.319
Going down
in that plane crash

10:54.321 --> 10:56.054
Made me feel like,
in the end,

10:56.056 --> 10:59.891
Maybe...Instead of being
terrified to die, she was brave.

10:59.893 --> 11:02.060
Maybe it wasn't so bad.

11:02.062 --> 11:03.795
Now...

11:05.731 --> 11:07.866
...It makes me think of you,

11:07.868 --> 11:13.872
And how you let me hate you
instead of telling me

11:13.874 --> 11:15.840
About
who she really was.

11:15.842 --> 11:17.776
What do you want,
olivia?

11:20.880 --> 11:26.851
I know that you've been replaced
at b613 as command.

11:26.853 --> 11:30.321
I work
for the smithsonian.

11:30.323 --> 11:32.857
My title
is chief curator.

11:32.859 --> 11:34.225
I'm just saying
I know what happened.

11:34.227 --> 11:37.829
I know how hard
this must be for you.

11:37.831 --> 11:39.764
B613 --

11:44.236 --> 11:48.773
The smithsonian...Has been
a big part of your life.

11:48.775 --> 11:49.908
I just wanted you
to know --

11:49.910 --> 11:52.410
What?
That I know
what happened!

11:52.412 --> 11:55.080
That I'm sorry, dad.

11:55.082 --> 11:58.817
You know what happened.
[ chuckles ]

11:58.819 --> 12:01.786
No, you have no idea
what happened.

12:01.788 --> 12:03.755
You have no idea
what is currently happening.

12:03.757 --> 12:05.790
You're skipping around
in a field full of bombs

12:05.792 --> 12:09.794
And mistaking them
for daisies.

12:09.796 --> 12:14.099
This, dear...
Sweet child,

12:14.101 --> 12:16.935
Is what happened.

12:16.937 --> 12:19.270
The married man
you can't seem to stay away from

12:19.272 --> 12:21.840
Had me abducted
and locked me up in chains

12:21.842 --> 12:23.141
And spoke to me
about the way you taste

12:23.143 --> 12:25.310
While he allowed the terrorist
who snaked her way

12:25.312 --> 12:28.480
Into my marriage bed
to clear u.S. Air space.

12:28.482 --> 12:31.216
What happened
was the man you <i>screwed</i>

12:31.218 --> 12:34.052
Betrayed me by freeing the woman
who gave birth to you

12:34.054 --> 12:35.386
As a bargaining chip.

12:35.388 --> 12:38.957
What happened was
the man who defiled you

12:38.959 --> 12:43.762
Also defiled an organization
that I gave my soul to build.

12:43.764 --> 12:46.097
That is what happened.

12:46.099 --> 12:47.799
What
is currently happening

12:47.801 --> 12:51.803
Is that president
fitzgerald thomas grant iii

12:51.805 --> 12:57.876
The worst kind of enemy,
because I know all his secrets.

12:57.878 --> 13:01.179
I know where every body
is buried.

13:01.181 --> 13:05.850
And the greatest weapon I can
use against him calls me "dad."

13:05.852 --> 13:09.187
Uncommon valor
<i>was</i> a common virtue.

13:09.189 --> 13:10.889
The thing
about that quote, olivia,

13:10.891 --> 13:13.525
Is that is from
the good old days.

13:13.527 --> 13:16.361
It no longer applies.
Today everyone is afraid.

13:16.363 --> 13:18.897
Everyone
<i>should</i> be afraid.

13:18.899 --> 13:20.899
The president
should be very afraid.

13:20.901 --> 13:25.170
And if I were <i>you,</i> olivia,
I would be terrified.

13:25.172 --> 13:27.005
I would pick up
whatever chips you have left

13:27.007 --> 13:30.508
And run as far away
as possible

13:30.510 --> 13:34.546
From that burning building
known as the white house.

13:34.548 --> 13:37.549
Run, olivia. Run.

13:37.551 --> 13:39.918
Because, mark my words,
fitzgerald grant

13:39.920 --> 13:42.187
Is not going to make it
to the end of his term.

13:45.925 --> 13:46.891
You wouldn't dare.

13:46.893 --> 13:48.827
Watch me.

13:55.167 --> 13:58.069
Start grieving now,
olivia.

13:58.071 --> 14:00.772
Rend your garments,
curse the heavens.

14:00.774 --> 14:03.074
It will save you time
down the road.

14:03.076 --> 14:06.044
But first, run.

14:16.121 --> 14:17.589
[ indistinct conversations ]

14:17.591 --> 14:19.357
[ cellphone chimes ]

14:38.344 --> 14:41.880
Oh. This one? Yeah.
Don't be nervous.

14:41.882 --> 14:44.382
I'm not nervous.
Worry about yourself.

14:44.384 --> 14:46.317
Me? Nervous? No.
Distracted? Slightly.

14:46.319 --> 14:48.887
Who could blame me?
[ chuckles ]

14:48.889 --> 14:51.422
But you might want to convince
your forehead of that.

14:51.424 --> 14:53.458
It's mighty shiny.
Ha. Nice try, bergen.

14:53.460 --> 14:55.560
Nose, too. Mm.

14:55.562 --> 14:57.528
Could you bring makeup to set?
I think she's having a little...

14:57.530 --> 14:59.364
There's no time.
We're on in 10 seconds.

14:59.366 --> 15:00.865
Don't sweat it.

15:00.867 --> 15:04.269
I mean, don't further sweat it.
You look fine.

15:04.271 --> 15:06.571
Regardless of legality,
this reckless move

15:06.573 --> 15:08.940
By sally langston threatens
our standing in the world.

15:08.942 --> 15:10.141
That's ridiculous.

15:10.143 --> 15:11.409
Sally langston
is doing one thing

15:11.411 --> 15:12.977
And one thing only --
her job.

15:12.979 --> 15:14.946
If vice president langston
thinks she can run the country

15:14.948 --> 15:18.616
Then she's free to run against
him during the general election,

15:18.618 --> 15:21.452
But she can't trash him outside
the gates of the white house,

15:21.454 --> 15:23.588
While working as the second
in command in the west wing.

15:23.590 --> 15:25.189
Again,
it's reckless behavior.

15:25.191 --> 15:27.926
How about hiring
your alleged mistress,

15:27.928 --> 15:29.360
Olivia pope,
as your campaign manager?

15:29.362 --> 15:32.063
Uh, I'm s--

15:32.065 --> 15:34.532
Those
unsubstantiated rumors

15:34.534 --> 15:36.434
Were put to bed
months ago when --

15:36.436 --> 15:38.102
[ chuckling ] um, that is
an interesting choice of words.

15:38.104 --> 15:39.537
Am I right, ashley?

15:39.539 --> 15:41.072
Leo, are you seriously
accusing president grant

15:41.074 --> 15:42.407
Of having an affair
with olivia pope,

15:42.409 --> 15:44.075
Even after
the president himself

15:44.077 --> 15:45.410
Named jeannine locke
as his mistress?

15:45.412 --> 15:47.512
Who's to say he had
just one mistress?

15:47.514 --> 15:49.380
He's a handsome man
with appetites.

15:49.382 --> 15:51.683
I choose not to underestimate
president grant

15:51.685 --> 15:52.684
In these matters.

15:52.686 --> 15:54.953
[ indistinct shouting ]

15:58.624 --> 16:01.192
Reporter: So, are you saying
that there's no truth

16:01.194 --> 16:06.097
This question has been asked and
answered to death months ago.

16:06.099 --> 16:07.398
Why hasn't the president
made a statement?

16:07.400 --> 16:09.500
[ indistinct shouting ]

16:09.502 --> 16:10.735
Again, I refuse to answer

16:10.737 --> 16:12.437
Any questions regarding
leo bergen's comments.

16:12.439 --> 16:14.272
We need to hit back fast.

16:14.274 --> 16:16.341
Change the story.
Leak some dirt on sally.

16:16.343 --> 16:18.443
If I had dirt, don't you think
I'd have dumped it by now?

16:18.445 --> 16:20.611
<i>Vanessa.</i>
<i>Why hasn't</i>
<i>daniel douglas langston's</i>

16:20.613 --> 16:22.580
<i>Autopsy report</i>
<i>been released to the public?</i>

16:22.582 --> 16:25.383
His medical records
are government records,

16:25.385 --> 16:27.218
Yet they've been sealed off
from the public.

16:27.220 --> 16:32.590
<i>Would there be a reason</i>
<i>that the white house</i>

16:32.592 --> 16:35.526
Again, I'll have to take that
question. Anyone else? Nathan.

16:37.363 --> 16:39.230
Leo: The entire
white house press corps

16:39.232 --> 16:42.500
Is pouring gasoline
on the fitz/olivia pope fire.

16:42.502 --> 16:44.602
Your approvals are up 6 points,
twitter's got you trending,

16:44.604 --> 16:47.739
And the radio is playing
"mustang sally."

16:47.741 --> 16:50.108
Ride, sally, ride --
they're calling you a maverick.

16:50.110 --> 16:52.176
The lies are unspooling,
leo.

16:52.178 --> 16:53.478
Someone knows about
daniel douglas.

16:53.480 --> 16:55.179
Someone knows
and there are questions

16:55.181 --> 16:57.015
And the lies are unspooling
and they will snare us

16:57.017 --> 16:58.483
And bring us down
in the fire of god's wrath.

16:58.485 --> 16:59.717
It is over.

16:59.719 --> 17:02.520
Sally...
We've talked about this.

17:02.522 --> 17:05.223
It is because
I turned my back on the faithful

17:05.224 --> 17:07.224
And condoned abortion.
Abortion? Really?

17:07.227 --> 17:08.526
Because
when I stop and rank

17:08.528 --> 17:10.028
The things
you've done sin-wise --

17:10.030 --> 17:11.462
I did not murder
my husband, leo.

17:12.431 --> 17:14.766
The devil murdered my husband
when he snuck inside me.

17:14.768 --> 17:16.534
And the reason
I was not vigilant,

17:16.536 --> 17:18.036
The reason
that I did not rise up

17:18.038 --> 17:19.670
And turn the devil away
from my gate

17:19.672 --> 17:21.105
Is that he distracted me.

17:21.107 --> 17:22.272
With pride,
he distracted me

17:22.275 --> 17:24.108
Into turning my back
on my flock,

17:24.109 --> 17:26.743
Into abandoning
the innocent unborn.

17:26.746 --> 17:29.347
I was distracted, and I let
the devil inside of me,

17:29.349 --> 17:31.349
And he used my hand
as a vessel of murder,

17:31.351 --> 17:32.650
A vessel of sin.

17:35.054 --> 17:36.654
Sir, please.
It's all right, sweetheart.
I work here.

17:36.656 --> 17:38.356
Since
we're neighbors now,

17:38.358 --> 17:40.591
I thought I'd stroll
down the hall and say hi.

17:40.593 --> 17:42.593
I'm calling security.

17:42.595 --> 17:44.429
There's no electioneering
in the white house.

17:44.431 --> 17:46.431
Special assistant
to the vice president.

17:46.433 --> 17:47.765
Anyway,
nobody follows that rule.

17:47.767 --> 17:51.269
Is that why olivia pope's
roaming the halls?

17:51.271 --> 17:53.404
[ sighs ]

17:53.406 --> 17:56.507
What do you want,
leo?

17:56.509 --> 17:59.343
The art's a little old man-y
for my taste,

17:59.345 --> 18:01.512
But I'm sure I could have them
hip it up for me.

18:01.514 --> 18:04.715
Are on a bullet train
to political oblivion.

18:04.717 --> 18:07.418
I've got two words for you --
ralph nader.

18:07.420 --> 18:09.387
[ scoffs ]
oh, wait! Two more --
ross perot.

18:09.389 --> 18:11.289
Try these two --
teddy roosevelt.

18:11.291 --> 18:12.457
He lost
his third-party race.

18:12.459 --> 18:14.158
His face
is on a mountain.

18:14.160 --> 18:16.461
Don't push me, leo.

18:16.463 --> 18:20.798
I know sally langston very well,
and I have no qualms

18:20.800 --> 18:23.334
About exposing her
for the pro-life, homophobic,

18:23.336 --> 18:25.736
Raging bitch
that she really is.

18:25.738 --> 18:27.271
As opposed to the corpse-moving
obstructor of justice

18:27.273 --> 18:28.473
That you are?

18:28.475 --> 18:30.741
That's right.
She told me what she did.

18:30.743 --> 18:33.111
More importantly,
what <i>you</i> did.

18:33.113 --> 18:35.780
So, go ahead.
Get right on that.

18:40.185 --> 18:41.519
So, what did he say,
specifically?

18:41.521 --> 18:43.321
Just that he needed some time
to think about it.

18:43.323 --> 18:44.555
I'll just look
for another job.

18:44.557 --> 18:46.557
I'll babysit,
wait tables.

18:46.559 --> 18:48.693
Hey. We both know
how great you'd be in b613.

18:48.695 --> 18:51.662
We just got to give command
some time to realize it, too.

18:51.664 --> 18:54.365
In the meantime, great thing
about our line of work --

18:54.367 --> 18:56.501
Rock-solid
job stability.

18:56.503 --> 18:58.436
I mean, as long as people
have to live together,

18:58.438 --> 19:00.371
Someone's gonna pay
to have someone else killed.

19:00.373 --> 19:02.406
Fact of life.

19:02.408 --> 19:05.510
Anyway, when I get depressed,
I always like to go shopping.

19:05.512 --> 19:07.445
Can I help you two
find something?

19:07.447 --> 19:09.780
Yeah, we're outfitting
my girlfriend's first tool box.

19:09.782 --> 19:12.450
Oh.
You know, so she can put up
some bookshelves.

19:12.452 --> 19:14.852
Every home needs a great set
of tools. [ chuckles ]

19:14.854 --> 19:16.854
Truer words, terry.
Truer words.

19:16.856 --> 19:19.423
[ cellphone rings ]
oh.

19:19.425 --> 19:20.892
[ beep ]
hey, boss.

19:20.894 --> 19:23.427
I need a mop-up job
on your last assignment.

19:23.429 --> 19:25.396
Can I still count on you
for some under-the-table work.

19:25.398 --> 19:26.664
Of course.

19:26.666 --> 19:28.232
Wouldn't want
that yelp review

19:28.234 --> 19:30.368
To say I was anything less
than thorough and discreet.

19:30.370 --> 19:32.203
Looks like
the dry spell's over.
Really?

19:32.205 --> 19:34.672
What did I say?
There's always work.

19:34.674 --> 19:36.541
Do you have power drills
around here?

19:36.543 --> 19:38.342
Maybe something
in a blow torch?

19:38.344 --> 19:39.377
For a book shelf?

19:39.379 --> 19:41.445
We're big readers.

19:43.215 --> 19:45.683
Bye!
See you tomorrow!

19:45.685 --> 19:47.485
Hi, billy. Hey!

19:47.487 --> 19:49.253
Hey -- oh, wait up.

19:49.255 --> 19:51.355
I'm not supposed
to talk to strangers.

19:51.357 --> 19:52.757
[ chuckles ]
I'm not a stranger, silly.

19:52.759 --> 19:55.426
She asked me to pick you up,
take you home.

19:55.428 --> 19:56.894
She had to work late.
How do you know my mom?

19:56.896 --> 19:58.229
Through your sister,
caitlin,

19:58.231 --> 19:59.564
Who plays softball
with my little sister,

19:59.566 --> 20:01.399
But she's not as good
as caitlin.

20:01.401 --> 20:03.467
Caitlin is, like,
really good, right?

20:03.469 --> 20:05.469
Yeah, she's got
a bunch of trophies.

20:05.471 --> 20:10.308
Maybe you can show me her
trophies when I take you home?

20:11.710 --> 20:14.545
That is,
after we get ice cream.

20:14.547 --> 20:15.813
It'll be our secret.

20:19.718 --> 20:21.485
[ chuckles ]

20:24.556 --> 20:27.892
Charlie: Seat belts.

20:30.229 --> 20:32.396
[ engine turns over ]

20:34.933 --> 20:37.435
James: I looked like
an incompetent fool.

20:37.437 --> 20:42.840
James.
Why wasn't there an autopsy
on daniel douglas?

20:42.842 --> 20:45.810
In order for me to stand up
there on that podium,

20:45.812 --> 20:47.545
I need to know
what not to say.

20:47.547 --> 20:48.946
We are not having
this conversation.

20:48.948 --> 20:51.983
Oh, god!
[ sighs ]

20:51.985 --> 20:54.752
Look at our baby, cyrus.
Look at her!

20:54.754 --> 20:58.889
Do you honestly think I would do
anything to jeopardize her?

20:58.891 --> 21:00.891
I'm on your side here,
so why don't you

21:00.893 --> 21:03.427
Just tell me the truth
and let me protect you?

21:03.429 --> 21:05.696
Refer any questions
about daniel douglas langston's

21:05.698 --> 21:07.898
Unfortunate death to the office
of the vice president.

21:07.900 --> 21:11.836
That's what you say.
That's <i>all</i> you say.

21:13.338 --> 21:14.672
He ambushed me.

21:14.674 --> 21:15.973
I had no idea he was gonna
make you the headline.

21:15.975 --> 21:18.309
He went low, which just means
we have to go lower.

21:18.311 --> 21:19.910
I want you and huck
to dig up everything we can

21:19.912 --> 21:21.445
On the death
of sally's husband.

21:21.447 --> 21:24.282
I'm saying there could be
more to the story.

21:24.284 --> 21:26.284
A question came up in the press
room today from a reporter

21:26.286 --> 21:29.487
Huck: Looks like
the reporter was right.

21:29.489 --> 21:32.556
Langston died of natural causes,
no autopsy.

21:32.558 --> 21:34.692
There's also no record
of who looked at the body.

21:34.694 --> 21:37.428
M.E. Never signed off.

21:38.497 --> 21:40.965
[ knock on door ]

21:40.967 --> 21:42.600
Can I help you?

21:42.602 --> 21:43.768
Hi.
We're from the <i>post.</i>

21:43.770 --> 21:44.935
We just had
a few quick questions

21:44.937 --> 21:46.070
About the coroner's report
you prepared

21:46.072 --> 21:47.738
On daniel douglas langston.

21:47.740 --> 21:51.909
Mr. Langston's blood had
elevated levels of troponin.

21:51.911 --> 21:54.412
I'm confident he died
of sudden cardiac arrest.

21:54.414 --> 21:56.013
Do you still have
those results?

21:56.015 --> 21:59.450
I shouldn't be
talking to you guys.

21:59.452 --> 22:01.786
Just let us
take a look at those tests

22:01.788 --> 22:03.421
And we'll be out
of your hair.

22:03.423 --> 22:05.022
They're gone.

22:05.024 --> 22:07.024
I destroyed them.

22:07.026 --> 22:10.561
I ran those tests against
the vice president's wishes.

22:13.332 --> 22:14.665
What's that?

22:14.667 --> 22:16.067
It's <i>new york times</i>
<i>best-seller material.</i>

22:16.069 --> 22:17.702
Couldn't put it down.

22:17.704 --> 22:19.370
Just two young lovers in mexico
on the hunt for cheap oxy.

22:19.372 --> 22:21.005
That was a long time ago.

22:21.007 --> 22:22.740
I didn't even know
my boyfriend

22:22.742 --> 22:24.375
Was trying to bring
anything back.

22:24.377 --> 22:26.010
Just tell us
how langston died, linda.

22:28.513 --> 22:30.348
[ sighs ]

22:30.350 --> 22:33.684
He was a big drinker.

22:33.686 --> 22:37.021
The night he died,
he took a spill in the bathroom,

22:37.023 --> 22:38.889
Smashed his head on the toilet.

22:38.891 --> 22:42.393
Massive brain bleed.

22:42.395 --> 22:44.061
I don't blame
the vice president

22:44.063 --> 22:46.030
For wanting
to keep that quiet.

22:46.032 --> 22:49.467
I really felt for her.

22:49.469 --> 22:52.636
Thank you
for your honesty.

22:52.638 --> 22:54.605
We'll bury this deep.

22:59.644 --> 23:00.845
[ door closes ]

23:00.847 --> 23:03.080
You've done good, linda.
Real good.

23:03.082 --> 23:06.917
Hey, billster, you crazy kid.
Get in here.

23:06.919 --> 23:08.519
Mommy!
Oh!

23:13.792 --> 23:15.126
[ sniffles ]
are you okay?
Mm-hmm.

23:15.128 --> 23:17.094
Oh, my god.

23:22.100 --> 23:24.668
[ telephone ringing ]

23:27.973 --> 23:29.140
Hello.

23:29.142 --> 23:31.108
Harrison wright,
it's your butler calling.

23:31.110 --> 23:33.844
I looked into your friend
adnan for you.
And?

23:33.846 --> 23:35.679
And I'm afraid deportation's
not an option.

23:35.681 --> 23:37.515
I called my contact
at immigration,

23:37.517 --> 23:39.517
And apparently
salif's visa was issued

23:39.519 --> 23:40.985
From pretty high
on the hill.

23:40.987 --> 23:43.087
Turns out your friends have more
powerful friends than you do.

23:43.089 --> 23:45.990
Some reservations
to a hot new restaurant,

23:45.992 --> 23:47.858
A massage for your tired,
aching should--

23:48.960 --> 23:51.996
What are we doing about
those daniel douglas rumors?

23:51.998 --> 23:53.497
I'm taking care of it.

23:53.499 --> 23:56.000
How?
Don't worry.

23:56.002 --> 23:58.035
Don't worry?
If you go down, I go down, too.

23:58.037 --> 24:00.171
And now andrew nichols
is our v.P. Pick?

24:00.173 --> 24:02.506
Don't patronize me like I am
some hysterical teenage girl

24:02.508 --> 24:04.041
At the beginning
of my cycle.

24:04.043 --> 24:05.676
There is plenty
to worry about.

24:05.678 --> 24:08.179
You want to worry about
something? Worry about this.

24:08.181 --> 24:09.980
You need to focus
on the big picture,

24:09.982 --> 24:11.682
Like getting your husband
to at least appear

24:11.684 --> 24:14.084
To prefer you
to his alleged mistress.

24:14.086 --> 24:16.220
It's not my fault fitz makes
googly eyes at olivia in public.

24:16.222 --> 24:18.189
Not your fault?
It's entirely your fault.

24:18.191 --> 24:20.724
Bringing in olivia
was your idea.

24:20.726 --> 24:24.061
Now, we have the predictable
mess of your making, so fix it.

24:24.063 --> 24:25.029
Do your damn job!

24:25.031 --> 24:26.997
I'm doing mine.
[ sighs ]

24:34.072 --> 24:36.841
Ah.
[ chuckles ]

24:36.843 --> 24:38.943
Smile, olivia. Smile.

24:38.945 --> 24:41.011
The glitterati are watching.
[ chuckles ]

24:44.549 --> 24:46.550
That's better.

24:46.552 --> 24:47.785
What are we doing here?

24:47.787 --> 24:50.788
We are sharing a meal,
being gal pals,

24:50.790 --> 24:52.990
Braiding each other's hair,
talking about boys.

24:52.992 --> 24:56.060
[ chuckles ] mellie.
Laugh. [ laughs ]

24:56.062 --> 24:59.563
[ camera shutters clicking ]

24:59.565 --> 25:02.833
I'm making a respectable woman
out of you, olivia.

25:02.835 --> 25:05.069
My husband can't be sleeping
with you if we're friends.

25:05.071 --> 25:07.071
I would never embrace
fitz's whore.

25:07.073 --> 25:10.074
I took the liberty
of ordering my favorite bottle.

25:10.076 --> 25:11.742
I know how you love
your wine.

25:11.744 --> 25:13.077
[ both chuckle ]

25:13.079 --> 25:16.747
Perfect.

25:16.749 --> 25:17.948
Oh, thank you.

25:17.950 --> 25:19.650
Oh, yeah.

25:19.652 --> 25:21.118
Oh.
Thank you, aaron.

25:22.220 --> 25:24.588
Why are you doing this?

25:24.590 --> 25:27.091
Because I like it when
my husband is the president.

25:27.093 --> 25:28.225
I worked very hard
for it.

25:28.227 --> 25:31.095
I've done a great deal
to get us here,

25:31.097 --> 25:33.097
And you are gonna get him
across the finish line,

25:33.099 --> 25:34.865
But you can't do that
if people know

25:34.867 --> 25:37.001
What kind of person
you really are.

25:37.003 --> 25:38.102
Cheers!

25:38.104 --> 25:40.104
[ glasses clink ]

25:40.106 --> 25:43.607
Now, I thought this public lunch
was a bold move.

25:43.609 --> 25:45.910
[ chuckles ]
and it is, isn't it?

25:45.912 --> 25:49.013
Bold, but just
the first step.

25:49.015 --> 25:51.582
I assume you'd know
better than me,

25:51.584 --> 25:54.752
What, with all your handling
and your fixing.

25:54.754 --> 25:57.087
Mm.

25:57.089 --> 25:59.056
There are the photographers
out front,

25:59.058 --> 26:00.991
Two tables back
is the gossip blogger

26:00.993 --> 26:02.860
For    <i>inside the beltway,</i>

26:02.862 --> 26:05.029
Behind me is the columnist
from the <i>dc daily,</i>

26:05.031 --> 26:07.064
And there's a woman from bnc
over to my left,

26:07.066 --> 26:09.099
Pretending she's not recording
us on her phone right now.

26:09.101 --> 26:10.200
[ laughs ]

26:10.202 --> 26:11.902
By day's end,
we'll be everywhere.

26:11.904 --> 26:13.904
[ chuckles ]
bold.

26:13.906 --> 26:15.072
Smart.

26:15.074 --> 26:17.141
Aww.
[ chuckles ]

26:17.143 --> 26:19.777
But, yes,
just a start.

26:19.779 --> 26:22.580
Which is what I thought.
Mm-hmm.

26:22.582 --> 26:24.081
This little lunch will work
for a few days,

26:24.083 --> 26:27.985
But the rumors won't go away,
not if you and fitz slip up.

26:27.987 --> 26:30.854
So, I came up
with step two.

26:30.856 --> 26:32.222
Ooh. What is this?

26:32.224 --> 26:33.757
A list of men --
eligible bachelors.

26:33.759 --> 26:35.593
Prominent, smart.

26:35.595 --> 26:38.028
Pick one.

26:39.864 --> 26:41.699
Pick one?
Any one of them.

26:41.701 --> 26:43.033
It's an equal
opportunity list.

26:43.035 --> 26:45.836
Tall, short, black, white,
republican, democrat.

26:45.838 --> 26:48.973
Just pick one
and start dating him.

26:48.975 --> 26:50.040
Publicly.

26:50.042 --> 26:52.109
So that people
can stop thinking

26:52.111 --> 26:54.244
That you're
screwing my husband.

26:56.114 --> 26:57.081
Smile, olivia.

26:57.083 --> 26:59.383
The world is watching.

26:59.385 --> 27:01.585
[ camera shutters clicking ]

27:08.927 --> 27:10.761
[ indistinct conversations ]

27:10.763 --> 27:12.896
[ cellphone chimes ]

27:27.846 --> 27:30.381
[ sighs ]
are you serious?

27:30.383 --> 27:32.383
You're stealing my gun.

27:32.385 --> 27:35.152
Harrison,
you do not get to act all crazy

27:35.154 --> 27:36.920
Just 'cause
everyone else here is.

27:36.922 --> 27:38.789
We are the normal ones.
You and me.

27:38.791 --> 27:40.758
If we need to borrow a gun,
we ask.

27:40.760 --> 27:42.159
Also,
why do you need it?

27:43.762 --> 27:46.163
Adnan sent me
that picture today.

27:46.165 --> 27:47.798
It's a business trip
to dubai.

27:47.800 --> 27:49.266
Adnan had a deal,
so we went to help.

27:49.268 --> 27:52.436
The other three people,
j.C., hammer, and ivy...

27:52.438 --> 27:54.905
So, what?
This is some sort of warning?

27:57.409 --> 27:58.409
It's a promise.

27:58.411 --> 28:01.779
Do you even know
how to use it?

28:01.781 --> 28:05.949
Or else you could
shoot off your penis?

28:07.419 --> 28:08.986
I know
how a gun works, abby.

28:16.861 --> 28:18.195
[ sighs ]

28:18.197 --> 28:21.298
Just...Be careful,
okay?

28:21.900 --> 28:23.734
Fitz: So, you're testing me
in front of an audience

28:23.736 --> 28:25.769
To -- what? --
Get my "q" rating.

28:25.771 --> 28:27.404
I'm trying to get past
your problem.

28:27.406 --> 28:29.239
I didn't know I had one.
You're a playboy.

28:29.241 --> 28:30.774
[ chuckles ]
come on.

28:30.776 --> 28:33.844
Starlets and socialites
and supermodels get called.

28:33.846 --> 28:35.179
One supermodel...

28:35.181 --> 28:37.181
Plus one
who was just swimsuit.

28:37.183 --> 28:40.784
That you even know
those distinctions is a problem.

28:40.786 --> 28:43.754
But you don't get
photographed with them.

28:43.756 --> 28:46.890
Like it or not, you're polling
as shallow, commitment-phobic,

28:46.892 --> 28:49.493
Closed off, unrelatable,
and therefore unelectable.

28:49.495 --> 28:50.828
So let's get started.

28:50.830 --> 28:53.897
So, why haven't you
settled down?

28:53.899 --> 28:55.866
The truth is
I love my work,

28:55.868 --> 28:58.368
And I tend to fall for women
who also love their work.

28:58.370 --> 29:00.370
Let's try again.

29:00.372 --> 29:02.873
Okay, but the answer
will be the same.
Then we'll keep trying.

29:02.875 --> 29:04.808
I'm telling you
the truth here.
Maybe you believe it.

29:04.810 --> 29:06.910
Maybe you've been telling
that lie for so long

29:06.912 --> 29:08.278
That you've
forgotten the truth.

29:08.280 --> 29:09.813
Let's try this --
what do you want me to say?

29:09.815 --> 29:11.448
That you're gay.
That you're a mama's boy.

29:11.450 --> 29:12.783
That you find
the idea of monogamy

29:12.785 --> 29:14.284
To be naive and unnatural.

29:14.286 --> 29:15.953
Anything but
the practiced canned answer

29:15.955 --> 29:17.287
You're trying to peddle me.

29:17.289 --> 29:18.789
This is ridiculous.
What are you afraid of?

29:18.791 --> 29:20.224
Why haven't you
settled down?

29:20.226 --> 29:22.893
I had my chance, okay?
I had my chance and I lost it.

29:25.196 --> 29:27.197
I let her go.
So I moved on.

29:27.199 --> 29:29.366
I married my job instead,
and I take great pride

29:29.368 --> 29:31.902
In what I've done
for the millions of californians

29:31.904 --> 29:33.137
Who have put
their trust in me.

29:33.139 --> 29:36.173
Maybe I'll get another shot
at marriage. Who knows?

29:36.175 --> 29:37.875
But what I do know

29:37.877 --> 29:40.511
Is that I'm not marrying
somebody I don't love.

29:40.513 --> 29:41.845
And if that
makes me unsuitable

29:41.847 --> 29:45.015
For the vice presidency,
so be it.

29:46.217 --> 29:48.786
Mr. President,
olivia pope is here.
Send her in.

29:48.788 --> 29:51.221
Thank you, lauren. Can you
close the door on your way out?

29:51.223 --> 29:53.190
Lauren, could you
leave the door open?

29:53.192 --> 29:56.527
Door closed, lauren.
Door open, lauren.

29:56.529 --> 29:59.363
I...I don't know
what to --

29:59.365 --> 30:01.698
Door open, lauren.

30:04.936 --> 30:05.936
Really?

30:05.938 --> 30:07.070
Really.

30:07.072 --> 30:09.006
And you stand there.

30:15.580 --> 30:18.582
I have all the numbers back
on andrew nichols.

30:18.584 --> 30:21.451
And?
They're good.

30:21.453 --> 30:22.853
He's good.

30:22.855 --> 30:24.154
But?

30:24.156 --> 30:26.290
Look, you want him.

30:26.292 --> 30:28.458
And I can spin it.
I can make it work.

30:28.460 --> 30:33.130
I can sell it to the people,
and you'll seem loyal and good

30:33.132 --> 30:36.133
And like you made
a great choice, but you didn't.

30:36.135 --> 30:39.136
He's wrong.
My gut tells me he's wrong.

30:39.138 --> 30:41.138
And mine tells me he's right.
You don't do this for a living.

30:41.140 --> 30:42.973
You don't run elections
for a living.

30:42.975 --> 30:45.876
I am president for a living,
liv. Come on.

30:45.878 --> 30:47.945
I should resign.

30:47.947 --> 30:49.613
Oh, liv.

30:49.615 --> 30:52.282
The rumors about us
are on every news channel,

30:52.284 --> 30:53.884
At the top of every hour.

30:53.886 --> 30:55.586
We're the headline.

30:55.588 --> 30:58.589
I can't do my job.
I can't run your campaign if --

30:58.591 --> 31:00.090
The news cycle will change.

31:00.092 --> 31:01.625
They'll find something else
to chew on.

31:01.627 --> 31:03.493
Your wife
took me to lunch

31:03.495 --> 31:08.098
And handed me a list
of eligible men I could date.

31:08.100 --> 31:10.567
She wants me
to get a boyfriend,

31:10.569 --> 31:14.504
Have someone on my arm
for show, like some k--

31:17.909 --> 31:19.543
I should resign.

31:19.545 --> 31:22.546
You are not gonna start dating
some man for show.

31:22.548 --> 31:25.883
And you are
<i>not</i> resigning.

31:25.885 --> 31:27.217
As far as the press
is concerned,

31:27.219 --> 31:30.254
I am a physical reminder
of the fact

31:30.256 --> 31:31.321
That you were unfaithful
to your wife.

31:31.323 --> 31:32.322
I am a liability.

31:32.324 --> 31:34.491
Fitz, door open.

31:34.493 --> 31:37.160
This is not -- door o--

31:40.965 --> 31:42.666
[ gasps ]

31:42.668 --> 31:45.535
You are not resigning.

31:45.537 --> 31:50.507
I refuse to accept
your resignation.

31:50.509 --> 31:53.176
You can't leave me.

31:53.178 --> 31:55.946
I am not
losing you again.

32:11.029 --> 32:14.031
Why did you put jake
in charge of b613?

32:14.033 --> 32:15.632
Who told you
that I put --

32:15.634 --> 32:19.469
You made jake
the <i>head</i> of b613.

32:19.471 --> 32:21.605
You know what that place
is like, you know what it does,

32:21.607 --> 32:25.142
And you made jake command.

32:25.144 --> 32:26.209
Why?

32:28.413 --> 32:29.579
Why?!

32:29.581 --> 32:33.550
I killed
329 innocent people.

32:33.552 --> 32:36.219
I let an international
terrorist, your mother,

32:36.221 --> 32:38.722
Out of the country,
and she killed three more.

32:38.724 --> 32:40.657
And no one knows
where she is.

32:40.659 --> 32:42.693
If I have any hope
of remaining president,

32:42.695 --> 32:44.962
Then it needs to
stay buried,

32:44.964 --> 32:47.597
And there's only one man I trust
to guard that grave.

32:47.599 --> 32:51.735
Jake ballard.

32:51.737 --> 32:53.737
[ chuckles ]

32:53.739 --> 32:56.606
What?

32:56.608 --> 33:02.112
You are stressed,
and you are scared.

33:02.114 --> 33:04.114
And you want this --

33:04.116 --> 33:06.616
You want to win this election
so bad, you can't breathe.

33:06.618 --> 33:09.052
And I understand that.

33:12.090 --> 33:14.091
But you don't trust me.

33:14.093 --> 33:16.660
I trust you!
Andrew nichols is wrong.

33:16.662 --> 33:18.762
He is not wrong!
Like I said!

33:18.764 --> 33:21.098
I trust you!
I need you!

33:21.100 --> 33:22.599
You want to win
this election,

33:22.601 --> 33:24.434
And you can't
do that if I --

33:24.436 --> 33:26.737
You are not resigning.

33:26.739 --> 33:29.106
I won't win without you.

33:41.719 --> 33:44.488
Liv.

33:44.490 --> 33:45.789
Liv!

33:45.791 --> 33:49.693
I'm not resigning.
I'll be here.

33:49.695 --> 33:50.660
[ door slams ]

33:50.662 --> 33:52.295
[ sighs ]

33:58.302 --> 34:00.070
[ creaking ]

34:10.047 --> 34:11.715
[ door creaks ]

34:11.717 --> 34:14.184
Put that away.
You look ridiculous.

34:17.088 --> 34:19.723
I don't
want to use this.

34:19.725 --> 34:20.791
But I will.

34:20.793 --> 34:22.559
No, you won't.

34:22.561 --> 34:25.094
Adnan.
I just want to talk.

34:25.097 --> 34:29.331
About your future, about
how we can help each other.

34:29.333 --> 34:32.569
I missed you so much,
harrison.

35:04.469 --> 35:06.336
Nice family.

35:06.338 --> 35:08.538
I mean, could use a mommy,
but --

35:08.540 --> 35:11.241
I'll give you exactly one second
to get your feet off my desk.

35:11.243 --> 35:13.510
Or I'll cut them off
and shove them down your throat.

35:13.512 --> 35:16.613
I seriously doubt my feet
would fit down my throat.

35:16.615 --> 35:18.348
I'm not talking about your feet,
you baby-faced twit.

35:18.350 --> 35:20.417
I'm talking about your balls.
Have they even dropped yet?

35:20.419 --> 35:22.786
Will you miss them
when they're gone?

35:22.788 --> 35:24.588
Up.

35:28.192 --> 35:30.494
Now out.

35:30.496 --> 35:32.362
We need to talk
about the leak.

35:32.364 --> 35:34.331
We don't need --

35:34.333 --> 35:35.799
Vanessa chandler --
someone is spilling

35:35.801 --> 35:37.501
The daniel douglas files
into her ear.

35:37.503 --> 35:38.435
She has a deep throat.

35:38.437 --> 35:40.170
Maybe it's me.

35:40.172 --> 35:43.840
You would be unworthy of that
title if you were that stupid.

35:43.842 --> 35:46.843
All you need to know
is I'm working on it.

35:46.845 --> 35:49.513
No, see,
<i>we're</i> working on it.

35:49.515 --> 35:51.781
Divided we fall
on this one, cy.

35:51.783 --> 35:53.750
Fine.

35:53.752 --> 35:55.218
<i>We're</i> working on it.

35:55.220 --> 35:57.454
Good.
Fine.

35:57.456 --> 36:00.423
<i>So, who else knows?</i>
<i>Who did you have do cleanup?</i>

36:00.425 --> 36:01.758
<i>Cleanup was professional.</i>

36:01.760 --> 36:02.926
<i>Secret service.</i>

36:02.928 --> 36:07.531
I thought you said
you were dropping this?

36:07.533 --> 36:09.799
I tried the dark side.
Turns out you were right.

36:09.801 --> 36:11.368
Didn't suit me.

36:11.370 --> 36:14.371
This whole time, you've
been standing up on that podium,

36:14.373 --> 36:15.839
Playing the good soldier.

36:15.841 --> 36:19.342
[ sighs ]

36:19.344 --> 36:22.379
My husband's a monster,
david.

36:22.381 --> 36:25.215
He's brilliant
and egomaniacal

36:25.217 --> 36:27.350
And has done more
to thwart the rule of law

36:27.352 --> 36:29.319
Than you and I
will probably ever know.

36:29.321 --> 36:32.622
He's a monster.
And he's powerful.

36:32.624 --> 36:35.458
And he thinks
he doesn't have a weakness.

36:35.460 --> 36:37.928
But he does.

36:37.930 --> 36:39.829
Me.

36:39.831 --> 36:42.499
And I will do
whatever it takes --

36:42.501 --> 36:45.335
Play the good soldier
and stand on the podium

36:45.337 --> 36:49.573
And sleep beside him
for as long as it takes

36:49.575 --> 36:53.276
To take
that monster down.

36:53.278 --> 36:55.478
Starting with this.
It's a good start,

36:55.480 --> 36:57.480
But the problem is
it's still inadmissible.

36:57.482 --> 36:59.416
Legally, at least one
of the parties

36:59.418 --> 37:01.785
Needs to know
they're being recorded.

37:01.787 --> 37:04.354
And god help whoever
it is who's been leaking
this stuff to the press.

37:04.356 --> 37:06.690
If these guys figure out
who that reporter's source is,

37:06.692 --> 37:08.391
They're as good as dead.

37:11.462 --> 37:13.330
Oh, god.

37:13.332 --> 37:16.833
James, please tell me
you're not.

37:16.835 --> 37:20.437
I am publius.

37:20.439 --> 37:22.639
[ knock on door ]

37:34.752 --> 37:37.454
[ sighs ]

37:37.456 --> 37:40.991
Got a night off
from ruling the underworld?

37:40.993 --> 37:44.661
Liv, I received an order
from my commander in chief.

37:44.663 --> 37:46.329
I couldn't say no,
and I didn't want to.

37:46.331 --> 37:49.432
I can run that organization
better than rowan ever did.

37:49.434 --> 37:50.900
There are
good men and women

37:50.902 --> 37:52.702
Who deserve a leader
they can trust.

37:52.704 --> 37:56.706
Someone who --
[ sighs ]

37:56.708 --> 37:58.608
I can do better, liv.
I know I can.

38:01.379 --> 38:03.513
You need to
give me back quinn.

38:03.515 --> 38:04.748
I don't have her.

38:04.750 --> 38:06.516
Would you tell me
if you did?

38:06.518 --> 38:08.785
Or would that be classified,
one of the many secrets

38:08.787 --> 38:11.554
You're going to have to keep
in order to be command.

38:13.457 --> 38:16.459
Liv, I can find your mother.
Bring her to justice.

38:16.461 --> 38:17.594
We both know
what your father would do

38:17.596 --> 38:18.762
If he were still in charge.

38:18.764 --> 38:20.664
My father
wasn't always a monster.

38:20.666 --> 38:22.365
He started out
just like you,

38:22.367 --> 38:25.368
Trying to do the right thing,
trying to keep us all safe.

38:25.370 --> 38:26.469
I couldn't say no.

38:26.471 --> 38:27.971
You could.
I couldn't!

38:27.973 --> 38:30.440
Of the president
of the United States.

38:30.442 --> 38:32.375
Don't we all?!

38:32.377 --> 38:33.877
[ sighs ]

38:33.879 --> 38:36.413
Serving the republic.

38:36.415 --> 38:40.417
I always thought it was
a good thing -- a <i>great</i> thing.

38:40.419 --> 38:43.086
True service, a calling.

38:43.088 --> 38:45.088
Now I think...

38:45.090 --> 38:49.993
I think it eats at you
until you are not you anymore,

38:49.995 --> 38:54.564
Until you are lost, until
you can't remember who you were,

38:54.566 --> 38:58.068
And all you can see
is the greater good.

38:58.070 --> 39:00.070
All you can see
is god and country.

39:00.072 --> 39:02.105
And you're so busy
being a patriot,

39:02.107 --> 39:05.375
You forget to be a person.

39:07.745 --> 39:08.912
Liv, what's wrong?

39:08.914 --> 39:10.747
Nothing.

39:10.749 --> 39:15.418
Just...Vermont keeps getting
further and further away.

39:15.420 --> 39:17.087
[ sighs ]

39:17.089 --> 39:18.988
Vermont?

39:23.461 --> 39:24.994
[ sighs ]

39:29.066 --> 39:31.568
So, are you?

39:31.570 --> 39:33.403
[ sighs ]

39:33.405 --> 39:34.571
Am I what?

39:34.573 --> 39:37.507
Are you a patriot?

39:46.717 --> 39:51.054
Mellie: And, yes, it's been
quite a year for fitz and me,

39:51.056 --> 39:53.423
But despite
our ups and downs,

39:53.425 --> 40:00.497
...To the citizens
of this great nation.
You are angry, but I did the
right thing, and you know I did.

40:00.499 --> 40:02.866
There are no more questions
about our relationship.

40:02.868 --> 40:04.434
But I have some questions
about yours.

40:04.436 --> 40:05.402
I thought
you trusted jake.

40:05.404 --> 40:06.703
This is a bad idea.

40:06.705 --> 40:08.705
It's how I can stay.

40:08.707 --> 40:10.173
But you all
didn't come to see me.

40:10.175 --> 40:12.041
You came to see my husband,

40:12.043 --> 40:14.544
The president
of the United States of america,

40:14.546 --> 40:17.046
Fitzgerald thomas grant iii!

40:17.048 --> 40:18.481
[ cheers and applause ]

40:24.789 --> 40:26.790
Thank you.

40:26.792 --> 40:28.958
Thank you all very much.

40:28.960 --> 40:32.462
I'm very happy
to be here with you tonight,

40:32.464 --> 40:35.031
To make
an historic announcement.

40:35.033 --> 40:36.866
Now, some of you
may have heard

40:36.868 --> 40:40.470
<i>In the market</i>
<i>for a new running mate.</i>

40:40.472 --> 40:42.505
Who is it?!
Who is it?! Who is it?!

40:42.507 --> 40:43.973
Hey. Look who's back
on her feet.

40:43.975 --> 40:47.143
Sit down, have a sweet tea,
enjoy the show.

40:47.145 --> 40:48.511
It doesn't matter
who it is,

40:48.513 --> 40:51.815
Because papa bergen
is on it.

40:51.817 --> 40:54.150
Sorry about that.
Wow!

40:54.152 --> 40:55.552
You know,
I never realized

40:55.554 --> 40:56.820
People like you
actually existed.

40:56.822 --> 40:58.688
I don't know whether
to be excited or scared.

40:58.690 --> 41:00.857
Both.

41:00.859 --> 41:02.091
You should be both.

41:02.093 --> 41:05.595
There's a particular value
I looked for

41:05.597 --> 41:06.663
When making the tough decision

41:06.665 --> 41:08.598
Of selecting
my new running mate.

41:08.600 --> 41:11.968
It's a value that the american
people possess in spades.

41:11.970 --> 41:13.970
That value is loyalty.

41:15.940 --> 41:17.707
Long way from sacramento.

41:17.709 --> 41:18.942
You and me both.

41:18.944 --> 41:20.243
[ both chuckle ]

41:20.245 --> 41:25.014
[ indistinct conversation ]

41:25.016 --> 41:26.916
Madam first lady,
you look stunning, as always.

41:26.918 --> 41:29.486
[ chuckles ]
thank you, andrew.

41:29.488 --> 41:31.521
Cyrus: Mr. President?
Be right back.

41:31.523 --> 41:35.525
[ sighs ]

41:35.527 --> 41:39.929
Every day for the last 12 years,
I have dreamed of this.

41:39.931 --> 41:41.498
Being on a ticket?

41:43.000 --> 41:47.003
Being near you again.

41:47.005 --> 41:49.706
Fitz: So, without further ado,
I'd like you to meet

41:49.708 --> 41:52.242
The next vice president
of the United States,

41:52.244 --> 41:56.546
My former lieutenant governor
and governor of california,

41:56.548 --> 41:59.282
A man I consider a brother
as much as a friend,

41:59.284 --> 42:01.284
Governor andrew nichols!

42:01.286 --> 42:02.585
[ cheers and applause ]
